            "__cdata": "<p class=\"p_20\">49. A 58-year-old secretary presents with asthenia and hyperpigmented changes on her elbows and inner cheek. She also has noted her blood pressure is low and she is dizzy when she stands. She has lost 10 pounds and has some nausea but no vomiting. A recent test for coccidioidomycosis was positive. Appropriate testing at this time includes?</p>"
